l:</div><div><br></div><div>Mandate Stronger Protections: Require platforms to implement robust content moderation systems and enhanced privacy controls.</div><div><br></div><div>Enforce Ethical Practices: Penalize companies that prioritize profits over user safety and well-being.</div><div><br></div><div>Increase Transparency: Ensure platforms disclose how their algorithms work and give users more control over their data and feeds.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>4. Build Age-Appropriate Experiences</div><div><br></div><div>Rather than banning children outright, we can create spaces designed specifically for younger users. The Emergence Party will:</div><div><br></div><div>Support Child-Friendly Platforms: Develop and promote social media platforms tailored to the needs of children, with enhanced safety features and strict content moderation.</div><div><br></div><div>Introduce Age-Appropriate Tools: Encourage platforms to provide tiered experiences based on age, ensuring younger users are protected without limiting their ability to connect and learn.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>---</div><div><br></div><div>Fostering a Healthier Digital Ecosystem for All</div><div><br></div><div>This isn‚Äôt just about children. Everyone‚Äîregardless of age‚Äîdeserves a healthier, more ethical online experience. By addressing the flaws in social media design, we can create platforms that:</div><div><br></div><div>Enhance Mental Health: Reduce anxiety, depression, and addiction by prioritizing user well-being.</div><div><br></div><div>Encourage Meaningful Connection: Shift the focus from empty engagement to genuine relationships and communities.</div><div><br></div><div>Respect Privacy: Empower users to control their data and online presence.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>---</div><div><br></div><div>Reversing the Ban: A Smarter Way Forward</div><div><br></div><div>Reversing the social media ban for children under 15 is not 